I think you already know what a base is. Now let’s go to Baseball 102. When no one is on base, you say the bases are empty. The opposite is that there are MEN ON (or a man on) base. This latter situation affects how the pitcher pitches, because certain motions he may make are considered deceptive to base runners, and if they occur, a balk is called and each runner can advance one base. When the bases are empty, the pitcher doesn’t have to worry about this. 

Bases loaded means there’s a runner on every base, so it’s a subset of MEN ON.

